message.entry: Entries in PRIM_POLY must be real positive integers.
Coefficients in PRIM_POLY must be between 0 and P-1.
The field parameter P must be a positive prime integer.
If input A is a column vector, then its entries must be real integers.
If input A is a matrix, then its entries must be real positive integers.
The second input argument must be either a scalar or a row vector.
M must be a real positive integer.
PRIM_POLY must be a monic primitive polynomial, see GFPRIMDF.
Coefficients in PRIM_POLY must be either zero or one.
PRIM_POLY is not a primitive polynomial.
